title: Re: Cosmo fangirls over Beyonce’s ‘bump’ at Grammys, is slapped HARD with their own hypocrisy
text:
Oh sad, silly Cosmo, you’ve been a proponent of abortion for years and years so you’ll have to forgive us for mocking your sudden adoration for this particular “baby bump”. Her fetus bump, right? https://t.co/CcgtTubuRX 
— Amanda Prestigiacomo (@AmandaPresto) February 13, 2017 Trending SHAME! NPR contributor (who also happens to be a refugee) charged with assault in DeVos 'protest' 
No no, it’s only a fetus when it’s not someone famous. Duh. @Cosmopolitan @Beyonce Remember that time you tweeted about more babies being born and followed it with a sad emoji? 
— Jeanne (@sleepy_jeannie) February 13, 2017 
We remember! But again, those weren’t famous babies being born so they didn’t count or something. @Cosmopolitan why is her bump a big deal? It's not like there is a baby in there or anything. It's just clumps of cells 
— Jordan Davis (@MGoJordan) February 13, 2017 
And really Beyonce herself is just a clump of cells … we all are. 
It’s science. 
— The Farisa (@farisa2020) February 13, 2017 
Hrm, good question. Guessing since it’s some magical baby in Beyonce’s womb the answer is YES. @Cosmopolitan @Beyonce is she pregnant with a child or a fetus? 
— Airborne Heel (@abnheel) February 13, 2017 
Unicorn.
